    <div class="inner-block">
      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Lucy Frazer QC was appointed as Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Ministry of Justice on 9 January 2018.</p>

<p>She was elected as Conservative MP for South East Cambridgeshire in 2015.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4542">
            <h1 id="parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state">Parliamentary Under Secretary of State</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>Her specific responsibilities include:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Court services and reform (including Bills)</li>
  <li>Legal aid</li>
  <li>Legal support and fees</li>
  <li>Administrative justice and tribunals</li>
  <li>Criminal justice</li>
  <li>Family justice</li>
  <li>Supporting the Secretary of State on EU exit and international business</li>
  <li>Shadow Commons minister for Lord Keen portfolio (except for Civil Liabilities Bill)</li>
  <li>Parliamentary Minister (SIs)</li>
</ul>
</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <a href="/government/ministers/parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state-for-justice">More about this role</a>
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
  <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice">Ministry of Justice</a>
</p>

            </div>
</section>      </div>




